## Import the dataset & load packages


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
fuel <- read.csv("../../../../data/qld_fuel.csv")
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
```
:::


## Distribution of Fuel Sites, grouped by Fuel type


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
fuel |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = Site_Latitude, y = Site_Longitude)) + 
  geom_jitter(aes(colour = Fuel_Type, label = Site_Suburb))
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}

```
Warning in geom_jitter(aes(colour = Fuel_Type, label = Site_Suburb)): Ignoring
unknown aesthetics: label
```


:::

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](QLD_fuel_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-2-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


## Most popular Fuel Type

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
fuel |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = Fuel_Type)) + 
  geom_bar()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](QLD_fuel_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-3-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::



## Price by Fuel Type


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
fuel |> 
  group_by(Fuel_Type) |> 
  summarise(mean_Price = mean(Price)) |> 
  ggplot() + 
  geom_col(aes(y = mean_Price, x = Fuel_Type))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](QLD_fuel_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-4-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::
